Dubai, United Arab Emirates &mdash; Best in-class companies to be recognised for their achievements and impact on business and society on 24th May in DubaiFrost &amp; Sullivan returns to UAE with its "2017 Growth Excellence in Best Practices Awards Banquet - Middle East" on 24 May, at Atlantis, The Palm, Dubai. This long-established awards programme is to recognise those companies in the Middle East that have demonstrated a unique approach to doing business in their markets, and that have delivered exceptional performance, with a major impact on business and society. Benchmarked against the highest standards in their industry, Frost &amp; Sullivan's awards recipients indeed represent the best in-class.Frost &amp; Sullivan follows its proprietary measurement-based methodology to select deserving companies in each category. Its industry analysts compare market participants and identify best-practice companies by measuring performance through extensive research, in-depth interviews, analysis, and benchmarking.The evening will kick off with an exclusive Growth Workshop for company leaders and their teams, all of whom are seeking opportunities to innovate and grow.Announcing the Frost &amp; Sullivan awards, Amol Kotwal, Director, Frost &amp; Sullivan said: "It gives me great pleasure to host best in-class achievers in the Middle East. The whole region has been facing challenging times due to lower oil prices, rising fiscal deficits and regional tensions. It is particularly important during these times to recognise those companies that - despite the aforementioned difficulties - were able to succeed and grow by transforming their business models. Our robust methodology coupled with detailed evaluation by an elite jury panel makes the Frost &amp; Sullivan awards the most independent and unbiased, yet coveted awards. We will be sharing success stories from the region on Growth, Innovation and Leadership."The awards will commend companies which demonstrate emerging trends and raise the bar across industry sectors such as Healthcare, Energy &amp; Environment, Metals &amp; Minerals, Mobility, Industrial Automation &amp; Process Control, Digital Media, Visionary Sciences, Aerospace &amp; Defence, TechVision, Logistics and Digital Transformation.This is an invitation only event and the awards bring together the top-notch executives from various industries, all under one roof. To find out more about Frost &amp; Sullivan's awards programme and partnership opportunities, please contact: khushboo.kapoor@frost.comThe "2017 Excellence in Best Practices Awards Banquet - Middle East" is supported by our Media Partners - Middle East Business Magazine and Arab Hospital Magazine.About Frost &amp; SullivanFrost &amp; Sullivan, the Growth Partnership Company, works in collaboration with clients to leverage visionary innovation that addresses the global challenges and related growth opportunities that will make or break today's market participants. For more than 50 years, we have been developing growth strategies for the global 1000, emerging businesses, the public sector and the investment community. Is your organization prepared for the next profound wave of industry convergence, disruptive technologies, increasing competitive intensity, Mega Trends, breakthrough best practices, changing customer dynamics and emerging economies?Media Contact:Srishti Choudhury,Sr. Events ExecutiveM: +91 89834 82489; P: +91 20 4077 8850E: srishti.choudhury@frost.comhttp://ww2.frost.com/Twitter: @Frost_MENASAEvent Hashtag: #FSMEAwardsFacebook: FrostandSullivanMENASALinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/frost-&amp;-sullivan